wikipedia_page.main: Helm Spencer (31 December 1891 – 7 December 1974) was an English first-class cricketer. A right-arm fast-medium bowler and lower-order right-hand bat, Spencer played for Lancashire, Glamorgan and Wales in 43 matches between 1914 and 1925. He was born at Padiham, Lancashire and died at Burnley, also in Lancashire.
